name: Sanke #2
description: Taisho Sanshoku, also formally named Taisho Sanke and commonly called Sanke, are a shiro (white) koi with hi (red) which is overlaid with sumi (black) patterns. Sanke don’t have sumi markings on their head and very rarely below the lateral line. These koi were developed in the Taisho era in Japan and were first exhibited in 1914
